This is the commit title; it should be short. Commit will highlight if it exceeds 50 characters (customizable).

Everything after the first blank line is the commit description. It can be as long as you like. Commit also comes with spel checkng.

# Please enter the commit message for your changes. Lines starting
# with '#' will be ignored, and an empty message aborts the commit.
#
# On branch master
#
# Initial commit
#
# Changes to be committed:
#	new file:   a.txt
#